what causes pneumonia i need to know the various things that can cause pneumonia what kinds of things around the house can cause it thanks firstly you're not going to get pneumonia around the house your house is the safest place you can be germ wise having another upper respiratory infection such as bronchitis or the common cold or even strep throat can precede pneumonia usually if a person has a strong immune system getting pneumonia isn't a concern unless they've had a respiratory or throat infection recently pneumonia is also linked to inactivity in the elderly young children get it usually due to immature immune systems i hope this helps Pneumonia Group A streptococcal infection Common cold Influenza Chlamydophila pneumoniae Streptococcus Upper respiratory tract infection Streptococcus pneumoniae Pathogen AIDS Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Common misconceptions about HIV and AIDS Immune system Legionellosis Bacterial pneumonia Haemophilus influenzae Avian influenza Mycoplasma pneumoniae Coronavirus Pulmonary alveolus Paramyxovirus Measles Infectious mononucleosis Asthma Otitis media Spanish flu Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Antiviral drug Medicine Adenoviridae Poliomyelitis Respiratory system Bioterrorism Acute respiratory distress syndrome Conjunctivitis Tobacco smoking Leukemia Respiratory tract Co-trimoxazole Psoriasis Urinary incontinence Transmission (medicine) Human papillomavirus Pertussis Duesberg hypothesis Traumatic brain injury HIV vaccine H5N1 Gastroesophageal reflux disease Lung cancer Timeline of AIDS Duchenne muscular dystrophy AIDS in the United States Cytomegalovirus Bronchitis Viral pneumonia Virus Biological warfare IgA nephropathy Allergy Respiratory rate Rheumatic fever Mycoplasma Childbirth Anemia Malaria Old wives' tale Anthrax Echinacea Biology Tonsil Diphtheria Toxoplasmosis Kaposi's sarcoma Cancer Staphylococcus aureus Premature birth Gastroenteritis Hay fever Sickle-cell disease Louise McIntosh Slaughter Rotavirus Chickenpox The Tale of t